comments: Beal (WAS) legally contests Hield?s (IND) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Mathurin (IND) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Mathurin (IND) legally contests Porzingis' (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Nesmith (IND) and Kuzma (WAS) mutually engage during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.
Nesmith (IND) steps into the frontcourt with his right foot and establishes position prior to receiving the pass from Haliburton (IND).
Wright (WAS) legally contests Nesmith's (IND) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Nesmith (IND) briefly places a resting hand on Beal's (WAS) side and the contact during the pass is marginal.
Nesmith (IND) legally contests Beal's (WAS) perimeter jump shot attempt.

Hield (IND) and Porzingis (WAS) launch into the air and reach for the ball. The two players get to the ball simultaneously and deflect it and the arm contact after the deflection is considered incidental.
Porzingis (WAS) reaches in for the ball makes contact with it and part of Smith's (IND) hand that is on the ball during the pass.
HT shows Mathurin (IND) gets his right hand to the ball and dislodges it from Beal (WAS), who is in the air and attempting to corral the loose ball.
Nesmith (IND) briefly grasps and releases Kuzma's (WAS) jersey as the two players elevate for the rebound.
Kuzma (WAS) makes hand on ball contact with Nesmith (IND) in order to dislodge the ball during the latter's power up to the basket.
Kuzma (WAS) jumps from point A to point B and into Mathurin's (IND) body, which alters the release of the reverse layup attempt.
Hield (IND) places and removes his forearm from Kuzma's (WAS) back and the contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal.
Porzingis (WAS) and Smith (IND) mutually engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity. The contact on the play is marginal.
Mathurin (IND) reaches in and makes some contact with the ball that disturbs Barton's (WAS) gather into the pass. The contact on the play is marginal.
Mathurin (IND) reaches in for the ball and makes contact with the inside of Barton's (WAS) left arm after the latter had gathered into his driving shot attempt.
Kuzma (WAS) legally contests Nesmith's (IND) perimeter jump shot attempt.

Replay review of the loose ball foul called on Hield (IND) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Hield grabs the left arm of Barton (WAS) and pulls the defender away from the rebounding opportunity as he launches towards the ball.
Gill (WAS) briefly grabs the arm of Smith (IND) during the rebound, but the contact is marginal.
